/golang.org/x/sys/execabs can move back to the default implementation  https://go.dev/blog/go1.19"},{"author":{"login":"mislav","name":"Mislav Marohnić","company":null},"body":"Thanks all for pointing out. This module is intentionally different from `execabs` and Go 1.19 `os/exec` in that simply ignores an executable found in the current directory on Windows, whereas Go 1.19 would throw an error in that case.\r\n\r\nAt GitHub CLI, we prefer the current directory be ignored (as it is with PATH resolution on other systems), so we're leaning in favor of this module rather than `execabs` or new stdlib."}]}},{"number":7,"title":"g","author":{"login":"dgsdoug","name":null,"email":"douglaslino79@gmail.com","company":null,"bio":"","location":"87970-000"},"createdAt":"2022-02-26T16:58:34Z","closedAt":"2022-03-08T18:13:41Z","comments":{"nodes":[]}},{"number":19,"title":"All issue","author":{"login":"fozourrahman","name":null,"email":"","company":null,"bio":null,"location":null},"createdAt":"2026-05-23T01:29:07Z","closedAt":"2026-05-23T01:29:26Z","comments":{"nodes":[]}}],"pageInfo":{"hasNextPage":false,"endCursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yM1QwMToyOTowN1rPAAAAAQyaRZ8="}}}}}]